Author: Krysia Andrews
Content: Grapes are often on lists of produce items with high pesticide residue levels, like the Dirty Dozen. While pesticide residue levels in conventional grapes are generally within safe limits, some studies show they are often found with multiple residues, including some suspected endocrine disruptors. Organic grapes are a good alternative for those seeking to minimize pesticide exposure.
